              margin-bottom: 15px;
            "><strong>The recent fall of Bashar al-Assad’s regime in Syria</strong> has given hope for the <a href="https://www.france24.com/en/live-news/20241217-un-says-one-million-syrians-may-return-in-first-half-of-2025" target="_blank">return</a> of displaced citizens after over a decade of civil war. The UN Refugee Agency (UNHCR) estimates that around one million Syrians may return during the first half of 2025.</p>
            <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.4;
              border-left: 3px solid #4c305f;
              padding-left: 14px;
              margin-bottom: 15px;
            "><strong>Gen. Igor Kirillov</strong>, a top <a href="https://edition.cnn.com/2024/12/17/europe/russia-bomb-kills-nuclear-protection-chief-intl-hnk/index.html" target="_blank">Russian general</a> in charge of the country's radiological, biological, and chemical protection forces, was <strong>killed in Moscow by a remotely detonated bomb planted in an electric scooter</strong> outside his apartment building.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="0px 12px" />
