              border-left: 3px solid #4c305f;
              padding-left: 14px;
              margin-bottom: 15px;
            "><strong>Honda and Nissan are reportedly negotiating a merger</strong> to combat rising competition from Chinese EV makers. The potential deal could create a single holding company, including Mitsubishi Motors. It follows collaboration on EV development amid industry challenges and declining profits (<a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/2024/dec/17/honda-and-nissan-to-start-talks-on-potential-mega-merger" target="_blank">read more</a>).</p>
            <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.4;
              border-left: 3px solid #4c305f;
              padding-left: 14px;
              margin-bottom: 15px;
            "><strong>The Center for American Rights petitioned the FCC to challenge Paramount's and Skydance's $8.4 billion merger</strong>, <a href="https://www.thewrap.com/paramount-skydance-merger-fcc-petition-center-for-american-rights/" target="_blank">citing concerns</a> over Tencent's (Skydance's majority shareholder) foreign influence and CBS’s (Paramount's owner) left-leaning bias. Earlier this year, a Paramount investor sued to block the deal, saying it would cost its shareholders $1.65 billion.</p>
            <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.4;
              border-left: 3px solid #4c305f;
              padding-left: 14px;
              margin-bottom: 15px;
            "><strong>Trump met TikTok CEO at Mar-a-Lago</strong> amid US plans to ban the app unless ByteDance sells it by 19 January. TikTok seeks Supreme Court intervention, citing free speech. At a press conference on Monday, Trump said his administration would "take a look at TikTok" (<a href="https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cre7vdz4npzo" target="_blank">read more</a>).</p>
        </mj-text>
