              padding-left: 14px;
              margin-bottom: 15px;
            "><strong>Researchers are using zebrafish to study how ketamine</strong>, an anesthetic, <a href="https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2024/12/241217130747.htm" target="_blank">affects</a> the brain and potentially treats severe depression. The fish exhibit a "giving up" behavior, which researchers use to study depression.</p>
            <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.4;
              border-left: 3px solid #4c305f;
              padding-left: 14px;
              margin-bottom: 15px;
            "><strong>Towana Looney became the third person to receive a kidney transplant</strong> from a <a href="https://www.technologyreview.com/2024/12/17/1108905/a-woman-in-the-us-is-the-third-person-to-receive-a-gene-edited-pig-kidney/" target="_blank">genetically engineered</a> pig at NYU Langone Health on November 25. After a couple of weeks after her surgery, she is off dialysis and in good health.</p>
            <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.4;
              border-left: 3px solid #4c305f;
              padding-left: 14px;
              margin-bottom: 15px;
            "><strong>SpaceX successfully launched two mPOWER communication satellites</strong> from Florida’s space coast today. The <a href="https://www.space.com/space-exploration/launches-spacecraft/spacex-launch-2-mpower-communication-satellites-from-florida" target="_blank">launch</a> involved a Falcon 9 rocket carrying O3b mPOWER 7 and 8 satellites toward medium Earth orbit.</p>
        </mj-text>
