              margin-bottom: 15px;
            ">A <a href="https://fifpro.org/en/player-iq/women-s-player-workload-monitoring/new-study-women-s-calendar-growth-is-fragmented-piling-too-many-games-on-some-players-but-providing-too-few-for-others" target="_blank">report</a> by FIFPRO <strong>highlights a growing disparity in women's football</strong>. Some players face overwhelming schedules of over 60 games a season while others play fewer than 10, which creates challenges for player health and development.</p>
